-- AXA UK CEO Paul Evans to head up British insurance industry body
-- By Simon Jessop
-- Tue Jul 01, 2014 09:19AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, July 1 (Reuters) - The chief executive of AXA UK, a unit of French insurer AXA <AXAF.PA>, will become the next chairman of the Association of British Insurers (ABI), the industry body said on Tuesday.

Paul Evans will replace Tidjane Thiam of Prudential <PRU.L>, whose two-year term ends on Thursday, the ABI said.